Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Dom Coleman

2023-03-12



My meme


This meme I title ‘Whirlpool of self-reflection’ encapsulates the emotions felt by one who leaves their project to the penultimate day before making progress. It signifies the individual feeling like a clown after failing to start the project early, leaving a situation of self-reflection and internalization.

Makes for good memes though!



‘Whirlpool of self-reflection’

library(magick)

#Storing meme image, scaling down & cropping the right side.
meme_picture <- image_read("https://i.imgflip.com/3yjodc.png?a466200") %>%
  image_crop("760x550-100") %>% 
  image_scale("450")

#Creating meme caption to go above meme image.
text_portion <- image_blank(760, 200, color = "#f0ead6") %>%
  image_annotate(" Telling yourself that you will start\n the project sooner than one day\n before the due date:", 
               size = 50, font = "Helvetica", color = "black") %>%
  image_scale("450")

#Combining meme image and meme caption text.
meme <- c(text_portion, meme_picture) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_border(color = "gray", geometry = "3x3") %>%
  image_write("my_meme.png")





My animated GIF


This GIF was made using original art of code on an old school computer I made in paint. I played around with the colors and border to make the frame transitions look satisfying!



‘Old school coding’

library(magick)

#Create frames of my PC art, adding background colors and cropping.
frame1 <- image_read("Old Code Desktop - White.png") %>%
  image_background("#96b18c") %>%
  image_crop("450x400-25+70") %>%
  image_border(color = "#e0e1d8", geometry = "5x5")
frame2 <- image_read("Old Code Desktop - Olive.png") %>%
  image_background("#e49d97") %>%
  image_crop("450x400-25+70") %>%
  image_border(color = "#96b18c", geometry = "5x5")
frame3 <- image_read("Old Code Desktop - Salmon.png") %>%
  image_background("#a5d9cb") %>%
  image_crop("450x400-25+70") %>%
  image_border(color = "#e49d97", geometry = "5x5")
frame4 <- image_read("Old Code Desktop - Teal.png") %>%
  image_background("#e0e1d8") %>%
  image_crop("450x400-25+70") %>%
  image_border(color = "#a5d9cb", geometry = "5x5")

#Combine frames of my PC art into a vector
pc <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)

#Animate flashing PC with nice background color and border
pc %>%
  image_animate(fps = 2) %>%
  image_write("my_animation.gif")
